{"body": "@rafaelfranca  Yeah, that text was confusing. I looked for something like that on the tests and all I could find were assertions with `joins`. I couldn't find any assertion stating that the `join` would be inferred.  \r\n\r\nAs for showing a full (and perhaps correct) example, I think it's already shown right above the line that was removed:\r\n\r\n```\r\nPost.includes(:comments)\r\n    .where(\"comments.name = 'foo'\")\r\n    .references(:comments)\r\n```\r\n\r\n@carlosantoniodasilva Isn't the code you posted, using `'comments.name' => 'foo'`, exactly what we are supposed to avoid from now ?\r\n\r\n", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/11152200", "created_at": "2012-12-08T00:29:39Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/8457#issuecomment-11152200", "updated_at": "2012-12-08T00:29:39Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 8457, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/caike/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/caike/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/caike/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/caike", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/caike/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/caike", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/caike/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/9958009345c43a8461e8673fbd0ae256?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F9e9aa9cfa4681a0bb8c946522067e902.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/caike/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/caike/received_events", "gravatar_id": "9958009345c43a8461e8673fbd0ae256", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/caike/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "caike", "type": "User", "id": 10722, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/caike/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237f2ffbd3543c15100a745"}, "id": 11152200, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issue